		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />For some reason, CRT TVs do make the resolution seem better, but I can't really explain why.
<br />
<br />I remember the first time I ran Sonic 1 on Genecyst back in 1997 or so and showed it to my father... The first thing he said was "the resolution is better on the console, right?". I knew it wasn't, but I understood why he'd think that. I don't know why, but CRT TVs are great at making low resolution content look good.

		

		</td>
