<br />
<br />Hell, I am not even sure what "forced to PAL" really means, they were Famicom (60-pin cartridges) compatible, but NTSC on a PAL TV produces a black and white image, so it must have been outputing actual PAL, just that console was hacked to support NTSC cartriges too, but pictures in PAL.

		

